A '''bio fireplace''' (also on '''bio-ethanol fireplace''', '''ethanol fireplace''') is a type of fireplace or furnace with combined zones generation of heat and technological process – combustion of fuel (denatured [[alcohol]]). This fireplace can be installed without a [[chimney]] and gives the real flame, not imitation. The main part of each bio fireplace is the burner. The burner is a metal container with various shape and [[dimensions]]. The [[Gas burner|burner]] is filled with fuel, usually it is [[bioethanol]]. Fuel is poured into the burner and lit with an extended candle lighter as suggested. Bio fireplaces should be operated with care, since bioethanol is highly flammable.<ref name=":1">{{cite journal|author1=Kraemer|first1=R|last2=Knobloch|first2=K|last3=Lorenzen|first3=J|last4=Breuing|first4=K. H.|last5=Koennecker|first5=S|last6=Rennekampff|first6=H. O.|last7=Vogt|first7=P. M.|year=2011|title=Severe burn injuries caused by bioethanol-design fireplaces-an overview on recreational fire threats|journal=Journal of Burn Care & Research|volume=32|issue=2|pages=173–7|doi=10.1097/BCR.0b013e31820aade7|pmid=21233730}}</ref><ref>[https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2014/09/140903091728.htm Ethanol fireplaces: The underestimated risk]. Science Daily (3 September 2014)</ref><ref>[http://www.staffordshirefire.gov.uk/2573.asp Warning About Use of Bio Ethanol Fuel]. Staffordshire Fire and Rescue Service</ref> Severe burn accidents can happen.<ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Heald|first=Alicia|last2=Muller|first2=Michael|title=Severe burns due to biofuel heater injury: A case series|url=https://doi.org/10.1016/j.burns.2015.04.013|journal=Burns|language=en|volume=42|issue=2|pages=e13–e17|doi=10.1016/j.burns.2015.04.013}}</ref> Bioethanol-fueled decorative fireplaces are dangerous even by intended use.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Neubrech|first=Florian|last2=Kiefer|first2=Jurij|last3=Schmidt|first3=Volker J.|last4=Bigdeli|first4=Amir K.|last5=Hernekamp|first5=J. Frederick|last6=Kremer|first6=Thomas|last7=Kneser|first7=Ulrich|last8=Radu|first8=Christian Andreas|title=Domestic bioethanol-fireplaces–a new source of severe burn accidents|url=https://doi.org/10.1016/j.burns.2015.10.004|journal=Burns|language=en|volume=42|issue=1|pages=209–214|doi=10.1016/j.burns.2015.10.004}}</ref> Gases from combustion, like [[carbon dioxide]] and [[nitrogen dioxide]], [[Volatile organic compound|volatile organic compounds]], and [[Particulates|particulate]] emissions are released into the room.<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Schripp|first=Tobias|last2=Salthammer|first2=Tunga|last3=Wientzek|first3=Sebastian|last4=Wensing|first4=Michael|date=2014-03-18|title=Chamber Studies on Nonvented Decorative Fireplaces Using Liquid or Gelled Ethanol Fuel|url=https://dx.doi.org/10.1021/es404972s|journal=Environmental Science & Technology|volume=48|issue=6|pages=3583–3590|doi=10.1021/es404972s|issn=0013-936X|bibcode=2014EnST...48.3583S}}</ref> Bio fireplace - irrespective of the type of fuel used are a source of fine and [[Ultrafine particle|ultrafine]] particles and have a considerable influence on the quality of the indoor air if ventilation is not provided.<ref name=":0" /> It may generate odors.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Nozza|first=Elena|last2=Capelli|first2=Laura|last3=Eusebio|first3=Lidia|last4=Derudi|first4=Marco|last5=Nano|first5=Giuseppe|last6=Rosso|first6=Renato Del|last7=Sironi|first7=Selena|title=The role of bioethanol flueless fireplaces on indoor air quality: Focus on odour emissions|url=https://doi.org/10.1016/j.buildenv.2016.01.004|journal=Building and Environment|language=en|volume=98|pages=98–106|doi=10.1016/j.buildenv.2016.01.004}}</ref>
== Types ==
Ethanol fireplaces are available in several different designs.There are manual ethanol fireplaces and automatic ethanol fireplaces. Automatic ethanol fireplace flames have no direct contact with fuel. Fuel is in stored in a reservoir and then heated until the alcohol vapors evaporate into the burner. These vapors are then ignited by a spark system in the unit. User can turn the flames on or off as well as regulate the flame size with a remote control, mobile app or smart home system. A microprocessor controls burning process, using numerous sensors to keep burning parameters stable. If the sensors detect any issues- such as an earth quake, low oxygen or excessively high temperatures- they will extinguish the flame. Wall mounted designs can be built into a [[drywall]] wall or be recessed into the wall. Free standing or stand alone ethanol fireplaces are portable, and can be used in any architectural setting. Table top ethanol fireplaces are the smallest versions of ethanol fireplaces and are often used as a decoration.
